Deutsche Bank Names Parameswaran to Lead Americas Media

-- B y   S e r e n a   S a i t t o
-- 
2011-08-09T21:49:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/deutsche-bank-names-parameswaran-to-lead-americas-media-1-.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ,  Germany ’s largest
lender, named Prem Parameswaran to lead media and telecom
investment-banking coverage in the Americas.  Parameswaran’s appointment was announced in an internal
memo, the contents of which were confirmed by  John Gallagher , a
spokesman for the Frankfurt-based bank. Parameswaran succeeds
Don Birchenough, who left to join  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  in May.
Malcolm Morris was named vice chairman for Americas media
coverage.  Parameswaran joined Deutsche Bank in 2003, most recently
managing Americas telecom, according to the bank. He covers
accounts including  AT&T Inc. (T) ,  Paetec Holding Corp. (PAET) , RCN Corp.
and Frontier Corp. Morris has been with Deutsche Bank since
1992, most recently as head of cable and tower coverage.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Serena Saitto in New York at 
